 for the three\nphases of Tb2O3. These results are thoroughly compared and discussed in\nrelation to those reported for rare-earth and other related sesquioxides. It is\nconcluded that the evolution of the volume and bulk modulus of all the three\nphases of these technologically relevant compounds exhibit a nearly linear\ntrend with respect to the third power of the ionic radii of the cations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 26 May 2020 18:18:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-05-28"}
